# Pre-requisite: Access to the jumpbox

If you don't already have a keypair you'll need to generate one - this will create 2 files in the **~./.ssh** directory:

  - **<KEY_NAME>** the private key  **\*\*NEVER SHARE THIS WITH ANYONE\*\***
  - **<KEY_NAME>.pub** the public key

  ```
  ssh-keygen -t rsa -f ~/.ssh/<KEY_NAME>
  ```

Paste the following snippet into the **ssh_admins.sh** script in the **rtx.environment.generator** package and assign the <PUBLIC_KEY_CONTENTS> to a <USER_NAME>

  ```bash
  if [ $(grep -c <USER_NAME> /etc/passwd) = 0 ] ; then
  useradd <USER_NAME>
  fi
  su -l <USER_NAME> <<EOF
  mkdir .ssh
  chmod 700 .ssh
  touch .ssh/authorized_keys
  chmod 600 .ssh/authorized_keys
  echo "<PUBLIC_KEY_CONTENTS>" >> .ssh/authorized_keys
  echo "cp /dev/null ~/.bash_history && history -c && clear" >> .bash_logout
  EOF

  sh -c "echo '<USER_NAME> ALL = NOPASSWD: ALL' >> /etc/sudoers.d/admins"
  sh -c "echo '<USER_NAME> ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD:ALL' >> /etc/sudoers.d/admins"

  sudo chage -l <USER_NAME>
  sudo chage -m 0 -M 99999 -I -1 -E -1 <USER_NAME>
  sudo chage -l <USER_NAME>
  ```

- <PUBLIC_KEY_CONTENTS> This is the content of the **rtx.pub**
- <USER_NAME> This is the username you will associate with the key pair e.g **yannis.hrisos**

In AWS > CloudFormation: drop the jumpbox stack.  Check in your changes and push to the remote, triggering a new release.  This will recreate the jumpbox stack and in turn configure access for your <USER_NAME>

Once the deployment is complete you will be able to connect.

# Pre-requisite: Ability to connect to the existing MongoDB

If not already installed, download and install Robo3T for whichever operating system you are running then open a terminal and open a secure ssh tunnel to the jumpbox.  Mac users may prefer to use the **secure-pipes** application.

**YOU MUST BE CONNECTED TO THE VPN USING THE EmployeeVPN-FullTunnel PROFILE IF NOT ON PREMISE AS JUMPBOX ACCESS IS RESTRICTED TO THE SAGE NETWORK**

  ```
  ssh -i ~/.ssh/<KEY_NAME> -L <LOCAL_PORT>:<REMOTE_HOST>:27017 <USER_NAME>@<JUMP_BOX> -N
  ```
ssh -i ~/.ssh/rsa -L 28888:10.10.200.3.117:27017 caoimhin.flood@ec2-52-215-151-82.eu-west-1.compute.amazonaws.com
  - <KEY_NAME> This is the name of the key that you created e.g. **rtx**
  - <LOCAL_PORT> This is port on your local machine that wish to bind to e.g. **28888**
  <!-- - <REMOTE_HOST> This is the cluster endpoint of the remote DocumentDb you are connecting to e.g. **rtx-ie-qa-testing-only-db-cluster.cluster-cizfmaphlclw.eu-west-1.docdb.amazonaws.com** -->
  - <REMOTE_HOST> This is the private IP address of the primary mongo node e.g. **10.200.3.132**
  - <USER_NAME> This is the username that your private key was associated with e.g. **yannis.hrisos**
  - <JUMP_BOX> This is the public DNS of the jumpbox instance e.g. **ec2-54-78-17-97.eu-west-1.compute.amazonaws.com**

# Pre-requisite: Ability to connect to the new DocumentDB cluster

If not already installed, download and install Robo3T for whichever operating system you are running then open a terminal and open a secure ssh tunnel to the jumpbox.  Mac users may prefer to use the **secure-pipes** application.

**YOU MUST BE CONNECTED TO THE VPN USING THE EmployeeVPN-FullTunnel PROFILE IF NOT ON PREMISE AS JUMPBOX ACCESS IS RESTRICTED TO THE SAGE NETWORK**

  ```
  ssh -i ~/.ssh/<KEY_NAME> -L <LOCAL_PORT>:<REMOTE_HOST>:27017 <USER_NAME>@<JUMP_BOX> -N
  ```

  - <KEY_NAME> This is the name of the key that you created e.g. **rtx**
  - <LOCAL_PORT> This is port on your local machine that wish to bind to e.g. **28889**
  - <REMOTE_HOST> This is the cluster endpoint of the remote DocumentDb you are connecting to e.g. **rtx-ie-qa-testing-only-db-cluster.cluster-cizfmaphlclw.eu-west-1.docdb.amazonaws.com**
  - <USER_NAME> This is the username that your private key was associated with e.g. **yannis.hrisos**
  - <JUMP_BOX> This is the public DNS of the jumpbox instance e.g. **ec2-54-78-17-97.eu-west-1.compute.amazonaws.com**


Download the Amazon RDS certificate authority (CA) file

```
curl -o <PATH_TO_DOWNLOADS>/rds-combined-ca-bundle.pem https://s3.amazonaws.com/rds-downloads/rds-combined-ca-bundle.pem
```

  - <PATH_TO_DOWNLOADS> Wherever you want to download the file to e.g. **/home/yannis.hrisos/Downloads**

Create a new connection in Robo3T
